    "It is also possible to interchange phase and amplitude.",
    "For instance, as shown in Fig. 1c, two phase-only functions of opposite sign, expð ± iXÞ, can be added to produce an amplitude-only function, cosðXÞ.",
    "In the context of OAM, this means adding two OAM modes of opposite topological charge, as shown in the example X = ±3ϕ.",
